# 🧠 Fake News Detection 

An intelligent web-based system that detects **fake news, image morphing, and video deepfakes** using a combination of **machine learning, deep learning, and real-time verification techniques**.

---

## 🌟 Key Features

* 📰 **Fake News Detection (Text)**

  * Real vs Fake classification
  * Real-time verification using Google Search API
  * Multilingual support with automatic translation
  * Displays credible source links

* 🖼️ **Image Morphing Detection**

  * Detects morphed vs original images
  * Custom CNN model built using PyTorch

* 🎥 **Video Deepfake Detection**

  * Frame-based analysis using OpenCV
  * Deepfake vs authentic classification

* 📊 **Interactive UI**

  * Tab-based navigation (Text / Image / Video)
  * Animated accuracy bars
  * Modern glassmorphism design

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Frontend**

* HTML, CSS, JavaScript

**Backend**

* Flask (Python)

**AI / ML**

* PyTorch (CNN model)
* OpenCV (video processing)
* Google Custom Search API
* Google Translate API

---

## ⚙️ Project Structure

```bash
FND_2025/
│
├── templates/
│   └── index.html          # Main frontend UI
│
├── static/
│   ├── style.css           # UI styling
│   ├── script.js           # Frontend logic (API calls)
│   └── uploads/            # Uploaded files (images/videos)
│
├── dataset/                # Training dataset (real & morphed)
│
├── app.py                  # Main Flask backend
├── train_model.py          # CNN model training script
├── extract_dataset.py      # Dataset extraction script
├── morph_model.pth         # Trained model file
│
├── requirements.txt        # Dependencies
├── .env                    # API keys (not pushed to GitHub)
├── .gitignore              # Ignored files
├── LICENSE                 # MIT License
└── README.md               # Project documentation
```

---

## ▶️ Getting Started

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/fake-news-detector.git
cd fake-news-detector
```

### 2. Setup Virtual Environment

```bash
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 3. Install Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 4. Add Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file:

```env
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_api_key
GOOGLE_CX=your_search_engine_id
```

### 5. Run the Application

```bash
python app.py
```

---

## 🧠 How It Works

* **Text Detection**

  * Translates input → analyzes keywords, domains, and patterns → verifies with web sources 

* **Image Detection**

  * Processes image → CNN model → predicts morphed/original

* **Video Detection**

  * Extracts frames → analyzes using CNN → aggregates prediction

